===Etymology===
Possibly from {{der|zh|sit-pro|*gaŋ||penis, male}} (STEDT), cognate with {{cog|mjw|chò-kàng|chò-'''kàng'''|penis}}, {{cog|grt|ri-gong|ri-'''gong'''|penis}}, {{cog|lep|ᰠᰫᰵᰃᰦᰵ|tr=sun̊-'''gan̊'''|t=penis}}, {{cog|lae|gàŋ mì|'''gàŋ''' mì|male}}.

However, Zev Handel doubts the Old Chinese word's cognate status, as "OC labialized initial plus schwa vocalism would normally correspond to a rounded vowel in PTB".

